{"TopicId":144915,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"KerbalSeats (custom, mod)","CreatedByName":"Climberfx","CreatedById":57126,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T21:45:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Climberfx","CreatedById":57126,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T21:45:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t find a way to have my Kerbal seat (custom one, that i made) to have the Tag when it is in use, appear used.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt always appear like there is no one seated in there!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there any flag i must discriminate in unity after i export the .mu file? Like it have in stairs (Tag Ladder, and Part Triggers in layer 21).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan any one help me?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.flickr.com/photos/climberfx/28552041022/in/dateposted-public/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Screen Shot 2016-07-30 at 6.43.21 PM\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://farm9.staticflickr.com/8422/28552041022_b23b9759b3.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.flickr.com/photos/climberfx/28552041192/in/dateposted-public/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Screen Shot 2016-07-30 at 6.43.31 PM\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://farm8.staticflickr.com/7764/28552041192_bf2ff7d86a_m.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.flickr.com/photos/climberfx/28658891255/in/dateposted-public/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Screen Shot 2016-07-30 at 6.50.17 PM\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://farm9.staticflickr.com/8857/28658891255_bfe4f8de48_b.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.flickr.com/photos/climberfx/28658891975/in/dateposted-public/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Screen Shot 2016-07-30 at 6.50.40 PM\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://farm9.staticflickr.com/8354/28658891975_bf98fd8240_b.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-30T21:52:52Z\u0022 title=\u002207/30/2016 09:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Climberfx\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T16:50:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, i thought someone would have chimed in by now,\u00A0 I\u0027ve hit some of the same issues, and although unresolved\u00A0 there\u0027s always a line or two in the log regarding Kerbal X has no IVA, The stock cmd seat has no\u00A0 IVA view,. have you created an IVA\u00A0 for the seat? You could get away with just the transforms for a seat and a portrait camera, no need for a model , the downside to this is that there is always going to be a black background to the kerbal, strange things happen if you have placeable seats and set the main parts layer to 16(kerbals) In my test it just turned the shell invisible to me but visible to the portrait camera\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Climberfx","CreatedById":57126,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T18:13:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool, if the IVA camera/view is the only thing i need to have it counting 1/1 crew in the part when in use, i gonna do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy seat are separated from the crew module part. Each seat is a part. For me is no trouble to have a black back ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGonna try it, thanks SpannerMonkey. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T18:48:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou will need to defin your IVA as InternalSpace in your Part config file as well.. If that is going to work.. Not sure it will or not, but let us know\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Climberfx","CreatedById":57126,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T20:27:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor sure JPLRepo. As soon as i try it!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheers commanders!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T20:30:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think what SpannerMonkey was suggesting is just define an empty Transform for the seat and an empty Transform for the Camera. Export that as a mu for the internal. (Assuming PartTools lets you do that). and define that as a Internal.cfg then add it to the part.cfg as InternalSpace.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf the PartTools doesn\u0027t work with just the transforms you might need to look at adding a bubble mesh around it that is transparent (so you can see through it to the outside).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Climberfx","CreatedById":57126,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T23:26:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, is what i understand, and what i gonna do! You can do only nulls objects, easy on Unity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-31T23:44:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222699350\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144915\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470007593\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257126\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Climberfx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, Climberfx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, is what i understand, and what i gonna do! You can do only nulls objects, easy on Unity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah - just not sure PartTools will create a mu with no meshes, etc. Never tried it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-31T23:44:42Z\u0022 title=\u002207/31/2016 11:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 31, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by JPLRepo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Climberfx","CreatedById":57126,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-01T01:12:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222699362\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144915\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470008662\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022114736\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JPLRepo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, JPLRepo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah - just not sure PartTools will create a mu with no meshes, etc. Never tried it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockq